sec.p:
Threshold regression refers to a statistical model for time to event data, in which the time to the event is defined as the first hitting of an absorbing boundary by an underlying stochastic process. We use the version of the IG model termed ‘Wiener Process with Absorption’ in the review by Aalen and Gjessing in 2001 [18] and previously applied in psychiatry by Crouchley and Pickles in 1991 [19]. In this model, the distribution of time to remission (t) is given by:
