Most explanatory variables (denoted x1, x2, …, xm) could be linked to both initial severity (distance from the remission threshold) and the rate of symptom improvement (velocity). However, randomised treatment or post-randomisation variables such as dose (denoted z1, z2, …, zm), cannot be associated with initial severity, but only to the rate of symptom improvement. Initial distance is linked to baseline covariates with an exponential function:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
