The residuals from the first-stage regression, Δ, can be considered as estimating the effects of other uncontrolled factors that influence a patient’s dose. In the second stage of this method, we estimate the survival model, but we include among the predictor variables the residuals from the first stage together with the patient’s relative dose, D:
